# daisyUI 5

## Setup (Tailwind 4)

In `src/routes/layout.css`:

```css
@import 'tailwindcss';
@plugin 'daisyui';
@plugin '@tailwindcss/forms';
@plugin '@tailwindcss/typography';
```

Optional themes in CSS (not `tailwind.config.js`):

```css
@plugin 'daisyui' {
  themes: winter --default, night --prefersdark;
}
```

Light mode uses **winter**; dark mode uses **night**. Theme toggle persists to `localStorage` key `docs-theme`.

## Usage

Prefer semantic daisyUI classes over custom utility stacks:

```svelte
<button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
<input class="input input-bordered w-full" />
<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">Title</h2>
    <p class="text-base-content/70">Body</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

- Use `btn`, `input`, `select`, `textarea`, `card`, `modal`, `alert`, `badge`, `navbar`
- Theme tokens: `bg-base-100`, `text-base-content`, `border-base-300`
- Combine with Tailwind utilities for layout (`flex`, `gap-4`, `grid`) — not for reinventing buttons/inputs
- Do not use removed daisyUI 4 patterns (`btn-ghost` still valid; check v5 docs for renamed utilities)
